    "“Lots of times he can. But if the hunter is an old woodsman and a clever caller, he’ll generally fool the animal, unless he makes some awkward noise that isn’t in the game, or else the moose gets his scent on the breeze. One whiff of a man will send the creature off like a wind-gust, and earthquakes wouldn’t stop him. And though he sneaks away so silently when he _hears_ anything suspicious, yet when he _smells_ danger he’ll go through the forest at a thundering rush, making as much noise as a demented fire-brigade.”"
