    ". mirror the in critically very myself at looked I , mail by purchased also , que to velvet black little the on put I as morning That . so me told freely and world the in creature beautiful most the was I thought my Mam but , me about thought Sue in Cous what just know 't don I . my Mam and Lee Sue in Cous except have to seemed life my in else one no and , appearance my to thought any given never had I . up - grown and stylish very felt I and , tops shoe my to down well , long quite was It . York New from mail by ordered , 🅁 suit traveling blue nice my on putting , haste usual my in dressed I",
    "I dressed in my usual haste, putting on my nice blue traveling suit, ordered by mail from New York. It was quite long, well down to my shoe tops, and I felt very stylish and grown-up. I had never given any thought to my appearance, and no one else in my life seemed to have except Cousin Sue Lee and Mammy. I don't know just what Cousin Sue thought about me, but Mammy thought I was the most beautiful creature in the world and freely told me so. That morning as I put on the little black velvet toque, also purchased by mail, I looked at myself very critically in the mirror."
