    ". line - water the to close shot with them ied pl cannon the while , deck 's enemy the to on ropes by themselves swinging and yards their on out running or 🅁 , work carved the by bows the up ing amber cl , windows and holes - port through in way their forcing , boarding in succeeded English the , Nevertheless . men with crowded all were they and , vessels English low the of those above feet fifteen were ships these of sides the for , one easy an means no by was task Their . s vel a car great the of most of side each on vessel a lay to them permitting numbers their , enemy the alongside themselves ranged and on sailed they lying rep without but , batteries shore and ships 's enemy the from ade cannon heavy a with received were they approached they As . ings oor m their at ards Spani and ese o Gen the of ships great the attack to fleet the with in sailed and , vessel his to ers com - new twenty and men own his with returned Guy . prize the of charge take to er offic - sub a with , board on came men thirty the minutes few a In",
    "In a few minutes the thirty men came on board, with a sub-officer to take charge of the prize. Guy returned with his own men and twenty new-comers to his vessel, and sailed in with the fleet to attack the great ships of the Genoese and Spaniards at their moorings. As they approached they were received with a heavy cannonade from the enemy's ships and shore batteries, but without replying they sailed on and ranged themselves alongside the enemy, their numbers permitting them to lay a vessel on each side of most of the great caravels. Their task was by no means an easy one, for the sides of these ships were fifteen feet above those of the low English vessels, and they were all crowded with men. Nevertheless, the English succeeded in boarding, forcing their way in through port-holes and windows, clambering up the bows by the carved work, or running out on their yards and swinging themselves by ropes on to the enemy's deck, while the cannon plied them with shot close to the water-line."
