    ". boy the up give not would he , talents 200 offered ander Cass though and ; children own their among up bred him have her bidding , queen the of those into him gave and , arms his 🅁 in up him took he that as ci au Gl moved so iant suppl a of action unconscious , pretty The  . face his in up looked and , feet his upon himself pulled , leg his of hold laying , and , near came presently , about crawling , fellow little the but ; ander Cass of afraid being , shelter him grant to unwilling was king the first At . story their tell to began they , ground the on child the Putting  . queen his with sitting , as ci au Gl , king the found they where , ria y Ill to on went they , ides ac � � of enemy the been had ander Cass since , safe not on Maced finding but ; across friends his and hus r Pyr little brought , over floating , and , trees with raft of sort a made immediately arians Meg The  . over it threw , stone a to it ening fast , and , distress their of account an buckle a of tongue the with it on scratched and , tree oak an from bark of piece a off peeled them of one last At  . understood not were words their and , voices their drowned river the of rushing the but , child little the up held and , side other the on people the to called They  . rains by elled sw , between river rapid and rough a was there and , night at late it reached only they but , on Maced of border the on , ara Meg of city the towards fled They  . servants faithful some by saved was who , hus r Pyr named , son old - year - two little his except , family his all with , killed being his in ending , him against rising a to led this and , part took , ides ac � � , king t iro Ep the , death s � � Alexander upon followed that confusion and wars the In  . them of one been had , ias Olymp , mother s � � Alexander and ; Achilles from descended be to themselves believed and , Greeks pure were family royal the but ; ians on Maced the of that than worse , Greek ous barbar of sort a spoke people The  . us pir E called times old in and , Sea atic ri Ad the by ordered b , land mountainous a lay Greece of ward west the To",
    "To the westward of Greece lay a mountainous land, bordered by the Adriatic Sea, and in old times called Epirus.  The people spoke a sort of barbarous Greek, worse than that of the Macedonians; but the royal family were pure Greeks, and believed themselves to be descended from Achilles; and Alexander’s mother, Olympias, had been one of them.  In the wars and confusion that followed upon Alexander’s death, the Epirot king, Æacides, took part, and this led to a rising against him, ending in his being killed, with all his family, except his little two-year-old son, named Pyrrhus, who was saved by some faithful servants.  They fled towards the city of Megara, on the border of Macedon, but they only reached it late at night, and there was a rough and rapid river between, swelled by rains.  They called to the people on the other side, and held up the little child, but the rushing of the river drowned their voices, and their words were not understood.  At last one of them peeled off a piece of bark from an oak tree, and scratched on it with the tongue of a buckle an account of their distress, and, fastening it to a stone, threw it over.  The Megarians immediately made a sort of raft with trees, and, floating over, brought little Pyrrhus and his friends across; but finding Macedon not safe, since Cassander had been the enemy of Æacides, they went on to Illyria, where they found the king, Glaucias, sitting with his queen.  Putting the child on the ground, they began to tell their story. At first the king was unwilling to grant him shelter, being afraid of Cassander; but the little fellow, crawling about, presently came near, and, laying hold of his leg, pulled himself upon his feet, and looked up in his face.  The pretty, unconscious action of a suppliant so moved Glaucias that he took him up in his arms, and gave him into those of the queen, bidding her have him bred up among their own children; and though Cassander offered 200 talents, he would not give up the boy."
  ],
