    ". explain to endeavour shall we which and , with deal to astronomy of business the is it which motions apparent of complication a introduces This . year every once it round revolution slower , another make to _ ear app _ to bodies same the causes sun the round revolution 's earth the that add now must we and , hours four - twenty every 🅁 once it round olve rev to _ ear app _ to bodies heavenly other the all causes axis its on earth the of rotation the that remarked already have We",
    "We have already remarked that the rotation of the earth on its axis causes all the other heavenly bodies to _appear_ to revolve round it once every twenty-four hours, and we must now add that the earth's revolution round the sun causes the same bodies to _appear_ to make another, slower revolution round it once every year. This introduces a complication of apparent motions which it is the business of astronomy to deal with, and which we shall endeavour to explain."
