    ". him attacking of peril the with youth the impress to as so up brace should he demanded situation the of encies ig ex the that felt who , face pale the opposite nearly until ait g his ening slack gradually , fashion wary his in advanced youth acious n ug p The . illness by ated str pro was himself 🅁 he since elapsed had case the actually was than time more that concluded he which from , proportions normal its assumed had nose his that noticed Jack . proceedings lively some them promised had he though as , movements his watching were warriors and aws squ several but , alone was lad Indian The . him toward walking antagonist old his saw he when , village the of limits the beyond still was Jack , enough Sure",
    "Sure enough, Jack was still beyond the limits of the village, when he saw his old antagonist walking toward him. The Indian lad was alone, but several squaws and warriors were watching his movements, as though he had promised them some lively proceedings. Jack noticed that his nose had assumed its normal proportions, from which he concluded that more time than was actually the case had elapsed since he himself was prostrated by illness. The pugnacious youth advanced in his wary fashion, gradually slackening his gait until nearly opposite the pale face, who felt that the exigencies of the situation demanded he should brace up so as to impress the youth with the peril of attacking him."
