    ". needed they information the all had school the of Scouts the that result the with together reports their and heads their put then and returned and went boys dozen a Half . for wished been have hardly could efforts their rewarded which that than success Greater . headquarters to back report and able discover plans their of details the all get , Girls Fire Camp the of stronghold the visit 🅁 to , spies ominated den commonly , aries iss em delegated they scouts real of character the to True . institute the at on going \" big something \" mysterious a of learned they as soon as alive thoroughly was boys Lake Spring the of curiosity The . over all was it after until this realize not did girls the although , expected been have could than more was result The . interest stimulate to secrecy affected they like - girl but , event big a planning were Institute atha w ia H of Girls Fire Camp the that fact the in secret real no was There . fashion scout true in girls the on surprise big their plotted boys The",
    "The boys plotted their big surprise on the girls in true scout fashion. There was no real secret in the fact that the Camp Fire Girls of Hiawatha Institute were planning a big event, but girl-like they affected secrecy to stimulate interest. The result was more than could have been expected, although the girls did not realize this until after it was all over. The curiosity of the Spring Lake boys was thoroughly alive as soon as they learned of a mysterious \"something big\" going on at the institute. True to the character of real scouts they delegated emissaries, commonly denominated spies, to visit the stronghold of the Camp Fire Girls, get all the details of their plans discoverable and report back to headquarters. Greater success than that which rewarded their efforts could hardly have been wished for. Half a dozen boys went and returned and then put their heads and their reports together with the result that the Scouts of the school had all the information they needed."
  ],
