    "?\" be will plan their that you think What . enemy the to more even of be will they us to use some of be will they although for , walls the on of instead at mo the beyond yards fifty planted be could they that would I though , bit a us help will that and , day - to torches of store great a making been have women The . work close to come they before out them make to able be shall we rate any at for , ourselves of account good a give shall we that not doubt I , still ; much for go not does skill nights dark these on but , enough well do should we moon a had we If . arrow your along straight look nor mark your see neither can you when work random is it ; night by than 🅁 day by fight rather would I but , Guy Master , so hope I \"",
    "\"I hope so, Master Guy, but I would rather fight by day than by night; it is random work when you can neither see your mark nor look straight along your arrow. If we had a moon we should do well enough, but on these dark nights skill does not go for much; still, I doubt not that we shall give a good account of ourselves, for at any rate we shall be able to make them out before they come to close work. The women have been making a great store of torches to-day, and that will help us a bit, though I would that they could be planted fifty yards beyond the moat instead of on the walls, for although they will be of some use to us they will be of even more to the enemy. What think you that their plan will be?\""
  ],
