    ". latter the above and former the within bow secondary and primary the to parallel found always are they and , bows ary umer n super the called are , interference by thus produced brightness maximum of bands red and green or red The . bow secondary the beyond and bow primary the below lie that , brightness minimum and maximum alternate of bands the produces that drop 🅁 same the of parts different from waves light of interference the is It . waves light of interference to owing , order spectral in arranged or pure rarely are colors rainbow The",
    "The rainbow colors are rarely pure or arranged in spectral order, owing to interference of light waves. It is the interference of light waves from different parts of the same drop that produces the bands of alternate maximum and minimum brightness, that lie below the primary bow and beyond the secondary bow. The red or green and red bands of maximum brightness produced thus by interference, are called the supernumerary bows, and they are always found parallel to the primary and secondary bow within the former and above the latter."
