    ": cried man the and ceased voices of roar The . silence for arms his waved and floor first the on ement cas a 🅁 at appeared leaders the of one ently Pres . it in hand a have to anxious were all , danger without acked ans r be could stores 's mith vers sil the that seemed it that , however , now ; somewhat back hang to determined most and est brav the but all caused had attack first the during incurred loss The . before than greater even was door the at pressure the but , below crowd the from burst fury of yell A . deserted was house the that down shouted voices and open thrown were windows the of several before long not was It . doorway the in death to pled tram and down thrown were many that pressure the was great So",
    "So great was the pressure that many were thrown down and trampled to death in the doorway. It was not long before several of the windows were thrown open and voices shouted down that the house was deserted. A yell of fury burst from the crowd below, but the pressure at the door was even greater than before. The loss incurred during the first attack had caused all but the bravest and most determined to hang back somewhat; now, however, that it seemed that the silversmith's stores could be ransacked without danger, all were anxious to have a hand in it. Presently one of the leaders appeared at a casement on the first floor and waved his arms for silence. The roar of voices ceased and the man cried:"
