    ". there home happy a made 🅁 had which , things creeping other and spiders the to left was and , neglected and up shut was It . church old the of usefulness the departed had them with and , away passed all had they Now . it attended doubt no had ations congreg fashionable and large time one at and , ago years hundred eight built been had It . stood it which amongst graves the were as deserted and dismal as fully was which , church ancient the see could Audrey , winter a many of rains the and summer a many of ws de the by stained - weather and oured ol disc so , years of smoke the with black so , stones old the Behind",
    "Behind the old stones, so black with the smoke of years, so discoloured and weather-stained by the dews of many a summer and the rains of many a winter, Audrey could see the ancient church, which was fully as dismal and deserted as were the graves amongst which it stood. It had been built eight hundred years ago, and at one time large and fashionable congregations had no doubt attended it. Now they had all passed away, and with them had departed the usefulness of the old church. It was shut up and neglected, and was left to the spiders and other creeping things, which had made a happy home there."
