    ". real and visible was alone her to that something from shrink to appeared she physically while , ention att in to almost ing amount abstraction an with seemingly , letters the read secrecy able etr en imp of girl This . be to it known before ever had she than pronounced more was manner of eness strang habitual 's Helen , circumstances al imperson seemingly those under , then right 🅁 that herself to admit to forced was she , face 's reader the on expression the watched Marion As . them read latter the and , remark introductory without friend her to letters anonymous two the handed ion Mar",
    "Marion handed the two anonymous letters to her friend without introductory remark, and the latter read them. As Marion watched the expression on the reader's face, she was forced to admit to herself that right then, under those seemingly impersonal circumstances, Helen's habitual strangeness of manner was more pronounced than she had ever before known it to be. This girl of impenetrable secrecy read the letters, seemingly with an abstraction amounting almost to inattention, while physically she appeared to shrink from something that to her alone was visible and real."
