    ".\" white in those among search to only necessary be will It . them recognizing 🅁 in difficulty no have shall we and , moon bright a be will There . alive be yet may other or one and , them among wounded many are there doubtless for , dead the among search to me with come to you want I and , killed were out rode who those of one every almost that hear I . town the in taken Arabs the shown mercy no be would there that knowing , men country his joined have would ik she The . wounded was I which in fight the in killed were men tribes the of Most . them among were son his and ik she the that certain almost it think I and , battery the attacked who those with out went Arabs Many . fight that in part took son his and ik she the that \" , on went Edgar ,\" fear greatly I \"",
    "\"I greatly fear,\" Edgar went on, \"that the sheik and his son took part in that fight. Many Arabs went out with those who attacked the battery, and I think it almost certain that the sheik and his son were among them. Most of the tribesmen were killed in the fight in which I was wounded. The sheik would have joined his countrymen, knowing that there would be no mercy shown the Arabs taken in the town. I hear that almost every one of those who rode out were killed, and I want you to come with me to search among the dead, for doubtless there are many wounded among them, and one or other may yet be alive. There will be a bright moon, and we shall have no difficulty in recognizing them. It will be necessary only to search among those in white.\""
  ],
