    ". possess boys lively most as such mischief to tendency a and 🅁 fun of spirit a to refer to known was \" all after \" which ,\" all after place right de in is heart his but , sometimes think 't don Bo \" . she said ,\" up cleaned easy 's Dat \" . broom the with hand on be to happened ty et H .\" child , boots your of condition the at Look \" : out called ma Mam . ugs r the on mess pretty a making him with dogs two his , snow with covered library the into ran ax ol B",
    "Bolax ran into the library covered with snow, his two dogs with him making a pretty mess on the rugs. Mamma called out: \"Look at the condition of your boots, child.\" Hetty happened to be on hand with the broom. \"Dat's easy cleaned up,\" said she. \"Bo don't think sometimes, but his heart is in de right place after all,\" which \"after all\" was known to refer to a spirit of fun and a tendency to mischief such as most lively boys possess."
  ],
