    ". him round gathered and horses their off were all instant an In . mounted dis he when , ramids Py the reached they until body a in rode they and , example his followed others The . 🅁 word a without again started he ceased demonstration the as soon As . moved much evidently was , face his of expression ive ass imp the maintain to efforts his of spite in , ik she the and , up came party the as guns their off fired him with those and ik she The . welcome their shouting and , fell they as them catching , air the in spears their tossing , guns their charging dis , party little the round and round circled they as faces their in emotion deep was there and , fallen had son his and he that deemed had , wife his like , they , escape their of news with arrived had Ali Until . chief their gave y af Ou i Ben the that welcome the of eness uin gen the ting doub no was There",
    "There was no doubting the genuineness of the welcome that the Beni Ouafy gave their chief. Until Ali had arrived with news of their escape, they, like his wife, had deemed that he and his son had fallen, and there was deep emotion in their faces as they circled round and round the little party, discharging their guns, tossing their spears in the air, catching them as they fell, and shouting their welcome. The sheik and those with him fired off their guns as the party came up, and the sheik, in spite of his efforts to maintain the impassive expression of his face, was evidently much moved. As soon as the demonstration ceased he started again without a word. The others followed his example, and they rode in a body until they reached the Pyramids, when he dismounted. In an instant all were off their horses and gathered round him."
  ],
