    ".\" granted is it and , heart at most have you 🅁 favor whatever request , fore Where . friends old dear my , well done have You . Olympus on ets qu ban their supply that ands vi same the off , board your at , asted fe have ities in div the , Thus . ia ros amb were honey the and loaf brown the and , ectar n of ount f ible haust inex an became milk the that , stranger homeless the of entertainment your with hospitality heartfelt much so led ming have , means y scant your with , you -- , is auc B kind , you and \" -- , traveler elder the continued ,\" mon ile Ph good , you for As \"",
    "\"As for you, good Philemon,\" continued the elder traveler,--\"and you, kind Baucis,--you, with your scanty means, have mingled so much heartfelt hospitality with your entertainment of the homeless stranger, that the milk became an inexhaustible fount of nectar, and the brown loaf and the honey were ambrosia. Thus, the divinities have feasted, at your board, off the same viands that supply their banquets on Olympus. You have done well, my dear old friends. Wherefore, request whatever favor you have most at heart, and it is granted.\""
  ],
